definition.value: An ADP-D-ribose with beta configuration at the anomeric centre.
An ADP-D-ribose with alpha configuration at the anomeric centre.

A secondary carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-[(4-ethylpiperazin-1-yl)methyl]-3-(trifluoromethyl)benzoic acid with the primary amino group of N(3)-[(4-methoxy-1H-pyrrolo[2,3-b]pyridin-5-yl)methyl]-4-methylbenzene-1,3-diamine. It is a potent inhibitor of discoidin domain receptor tyrosine kinase 1 and 2 (DDR1/2) with IC50 = 47 nM and 145 nM, respectively.

A furonaphthodioxole that is furo[3',4':6,7]naphtho[2,3-d][1,3]dioxol-6(8H)-one substituted by a 1,3-benzodioxol-5-yl group at position 5. It is a naturally occurring lignan extracted from Taiwania cryptomerioides and found to be a potential inhibitor of COX2 expression.
An acyl flouride that is acetyl fluoride substituted by an amino group at position 2. It is a carcinogenic agent which induces hepatocellular carcinoma in rodents.
A C12, omega-oxo fatty acid with a double bond at position 9; found in soybean, a metabolite of both linolenic and linoleic acids.
A monounsaturated fatty acid comprising dodecanoic acid having a trans-double bond at the 10-position and a 12-oxo group.
